## 🔵 LAYER 6 — Database Models

### `Emergency.js` — Core Document

```
Emergency {
  deviceId        ← IoT device that triggered it
  patientId       ← ref → Patient
  sensorSnapshot  ← raw sensor readings
  status          ← current pipeline stage
  priority        ← LOW / MEDIUM / HIGH
  queueSequence   ← FIFO ordering number
  etaMinutes      ← estimated wait when no resources
  aiDecision {    ← full AI output
    action, confidence, priority, reasoning, anomalyFlag, usedFallback
  }
  assignedBed     ← ref → Bed
  assignedDoctor  ← ref → Doctor
  timeline[]      ← timestamped audit trail of every step
}
```

The `timeline[]` is a complete, embedded audit log — every state change, AI decision, and resource assignment recorded chronologically.

### `Doctor.js`
Doubles as the **User** model. Stores both doctors and admins. Fields: `name`, `password` (bcrypt), `role`, `specialization`, `availability` (score), `currentLoad`, `available` (bool), `currentEmergencyId`.

### `Bed.js`
`code`, `ward`, `available` (bool), `currentEmergencyId`. Toggled by the allocation/release logic.

### `Appointment.js`
`patientName`, `patientAge`, `doctorId`, `time`, `department`, `reason`, `status`.

### `Patient.js`
`name`, `age`, `bloodGroup`, `riskLevel` (1–3), `primaryCondition`.

### `ActionLog.js` + `SystemEvent.js`
Audit log collections used by the System Audit dashboard section.

