## 🔄 Data Flow Summary

```
EMERGENCY FLOW:
Admin clicks "Code Blue"
  → SHMS_API.triggerEmergency({deviceId, sensorSnapshot, priority: "HIGH"})
  → POST /emergencies/trigger
  → Pipeline: QUEUED → AI EVALUATION → DISPATCHED → BED ASSIGNED → DOCTOR ASSIGNED → COMPLETED
  → Every step: Socket.IO broadcast → all browsers update live
  → Doctor sees new case → clicks Attend → clicks Complete → resources released

AUTH FLOW:
Staff logs in → bcrypt compare → JWT issued → stored in localStorage
  → Protected APIs send Authorization: Bearer header
  → authMiddleware.js validates → req.user populated

APPOINTMENT FLOW:
Patient fills form → real doctor dropdown → POST /appointments
  → Backend validates doctor exists + no slot conflict
  → Doctor sees it in their Appointments panel
```

---

## 📊 Key Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Why |
|----------|-----|
| In-memory queue + sequential worker | Prevents race conditions — one emergency at a time |
| `Promise.race()` for AI | Never hangs; fallback always dispatches |
| Socket.IO push updates | No polling; every connected tab updates instantly |
| Same Node process serves frontend | No separate web server needed for demo |
| Doctors collection = Users | No separate auth table needed |
| Seed on every startup | Guarantees clean, consistent demo state |
| Timeline array on Emergency | Complete audit trail embedded in the document |
| `deviceDedupWindowMs` | Prevents double-triggering from same IoT device |

